main event: Mrs. Patricia M. Hultman observed a bright, shiny object in the sky on August 6, 1964, in Jersey City, New Jersey.
interesting points: The object moved slowly and silently across the sky in a northerly direction,The object had colored lights around its edge,After the sighting, Mrs. Hultman became very excited and contacted the New Jersey State Police,The USAF representative interviewed Mrs. Hultman and obtained photographs of the object,The incident is classified as 'INSUFFICIENT DATA' due to inconclusive photographs.
sighted object: a bright, shiny object in the sky
witness description: Mrs. Patricia M. Hultman, who reported the sighting
